com.metamx.rdiclient

Class RdiClientConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.metamx.rdiclient.RdiClientConfig

  • public class RdiClientConfig
extends Object
    RdiClient config class. A builder is provided for creating an RdiClientConfig. The rdiUrl, username, and password are required.

    • Method Detail

      • getRdiUrl

        public String getRdiUrl()
        This returns the Metamarkets API endpoint. It is a required parameter.

      • getUsername

        public String getUsername()
        Your username, which is provided by Metamarkets. It is a required parameter.

      • getPassword

        public String getPassword()
        Your passsword, which is provided by Metamarkets. It is a required parameter.

      • getContentEncoding

        public RdiClientConfig.ContentEncoding getContentEncoding()
        An enum for indicating whether or not the client should use encoding and, if so, which type. Current options are "NONE" and "GZIP". Because events will be compressed by the library, you should not compress them prior to calling the client.

        The default is ContentEncoding.NONE.

      • getMaxRetries

        public int getMaxRetries()
        The maximum number of retries the client should use when unable to successfully post data to the API. RdiClient will use exponential backoff retry strategy up to maxRetries.

        The default is 20.

      • getFlushCount

        public int getFlushCount()
        The maximum number of events to be queued by RdiClient when "send" is called. When "flushCount" is reached, the client will attempt to post a batch to the API.

        The default is 2000.

      • getFlushBytes

        public int getFlushBytes()
        The maximum number of bytes to be queued by RdiClient when "send" is called. When "flushBytes" is reached, the client will attempt to post a batch to the API.

        The default is 921600 (900KiB).

      • getPostTimeoutMillis

        public long getPostTimeoutMillis()
        The read timeout to configure for the HttpClient used by RdiClient.

        The default is 30000 (30 seconds).

      • getMaxConnectionCount

        public int getMaxConnectionCount()
        The maximum number of http connections used by RdiClient.

        The default is 1.

      • isRetryOnBadRequest

        public boolean isRetryOnBadRequest()
        Whether the client should retry on HTTP 400 errors returned by the API.

        The default is false.

      • fromProperties

        public static RdiClientConfig fromProperties(Properties props)
        Creates an RdiClientConfig from a properties file. These properties are recognized:

        • rdi.url: getRdiUrl()
        • rdi.username: getUsername()
        • rdi.password: getPassword()
        • rdi.flush.count: getFlushCount()
        • rdi.flush.bytes: getFlushBytes()
        • rdi.connection.count: getMaxConnectionCount()
        • rdi.connection.timeout: getPostTimeoutMillis()
        • rdi.connection.retries: getMaxRetries()
        • rdi.connection.retryOnBadRequest: isRetryOnBadRequest()
        • rdi.content.encoding: getContentEncoding()
